column4:
Localization files are formatted like CSV so they can be easily edited,
however formatting has strict rules for easy parsing. Most of these rules
are already handled by Excel / Libre / etc., so you don't have to worry
about them in normal usage. However, if your localization file seems to
be corrupted, these rules may be helpful for debugging purposes...
- The first 4 rows can be arbitrarily long
  - The first cell of first row is used to store this block of instruction
    text
  - The first 3 cells of the fourth row is used as headers
  - All other cells in the first and fourth rows are ignored
  - Columns in the second row alternate between property and value (ex.
    ' foo | 1 | bar | 3.5 | ... '
    - Any whitespaces before and after the property name are ignored
  - Columns in the third row are exclusively comments for properties in the
    second row
- Every following line can include any number of cells, but only the
  first four will be parsed (you can use the rest as comments if needed)
  - The fourth column is an optional metadata column

column1: Set to 1 allow the parser to read this file, otherwise it will be skipped and the default English localization will be used as fallback
column3: Float value that scales font size of all non-dialogue text, 1.0 for full size.
column5: Float value that scales font size of all dialogue text, 1.0 for full size.
column7: The author(s) of this file, will appear in credits

column2: THEY SHOULDN'T STAND A CHANCE AGAINST OUR TECHNOLOGY.
column3: 我们的科技比他们强太多了～优势在我！

column2: This METEOR GUN will spell the end of humanity, and this time I'll use the biggest setting!
column3: 这个[陨石炮]会终结人类文明！我要把他调到...最大！

column2: Oh, and you all will have to be disciplined for your inadequency too...
column3: 你们这些小兵也要为消极怠战付出代价！

column2: Are you lost? This is the command center.
column3: 你迷路了？这里是指挥中心.

column2: Wait, you aren't on our side.
column3: 不对——你不是我们这边的！

column2: Now how do we get back home.
Now how do we get back home.
We've captured the specimen they call <var>Cat</var>.
column3: 我们捕获了这个名叫<var>Cat</var>的生物样本.

column2: All that's left is to eliminate any remaining magic and our job is done.
He's had this coming for a long time now...
Oh... you're looking for <var>Cat</var>? I'm afraid they've already been sent off.
column3: 哦...你在找<var>Cat</var>？它应该已经被转移了.

column2: You're going to have to go to space if you want them.
column3: 要找到它就必须...上太空.

column2: We're going to be going back soon too. Hopefully we didn't cause you humans too much trouble.
column3: 我们马上就要回去了，希望和你们人类以后可以和平相处.

column2: This whole mission has been quite cumbersome...
column3: 这个任务给你们带来了很多麻烦...

column2: Oh... you're looking for <var>Cat</var>? I'm afraid they've already been sent off.

column2: we're so cooked if these comms break bro...
column3: 兄弟...要是这个传输坏掉我们就完了...

column2: like it's actually over bro the Commander's gonna be all over us
column3: 真的兄弟...老大要下来找我们麻烦.

column2: he'll teleport down on this pad and start yapping up a storm
column3: 它要传送下来骂我们一整月

column2: nothing broke! i might be the goat
nothing broke! im the best tech support in the galaxy
column3: 什么也没坏！我是全星系最强技工！

column2: The folks at my rank aren't allowed to ride the saucers :(
column3: 我们这些小卒子向来不准坐飞碟 :(

column2: Ahahaha no one can stop me from riding the saucer now.
column3: 哈哈！我终于可以坐飞碟了～

column2: Oh... don't tell anyone I'm here...
column3: 呃...别告诉他们我在这里

column2: I don't feel like fighting in this war.

column3: 什么？你想要我们的<#e6e639>炸弹</color>?

column2: Son, we need to WIN. These no good aliens are trying to take our land, and I WILL NOT LET THAT HAPPEN.
column3: Son, we need to WIN. These no good aliens are trying to take our land, and I WILL NOT LET THAT HAPPEN.

column2: This table is where we simulate their attacks.
column3: This table is where we simulate their attacks.

column2: Let's see if you have any bright ideas. We NEED to win.
column3: 你也许可以提供一些新主意.我们[不许]失败

column2: You're lucky that was just a simulation kiddo.
Now quit playing, we have a war to win!
Now quit playing, we have a war to win!
You've defeated the main forces! The commander should be somewhere out there still though.
column3: 敌军主力已经被击溃了!但是指挥官不知道逃去哪里了.

column2: Great work kiddo! You can have the extra munitions.
column3: 好样的!这里是更多的弹药补给.

column2: They better think again next time they try and invade us.
column3: They better think again next time they try and invade us.

column2: What the hell you KILLED their commander?!
column3: 你[杀]了他们的指挥官?真的?

column2: Great work kiddo! You can have the extra munitions.
column3: 好样的!这里是更多的弹药补给.

column2: Do whatever you want with the skull, I don't need it.
column3: 这些骨头你随便处理吧,我不想要.

column2: We've only got enough supplies for one shot.
column3: 我们的补给只够发射一次.

column2: Phew, I thought we were left for dead there.
column3: 还好,还以为我们死定了.

column2: Hands off. Supplies required for military conflict.
Nice job! I knew you could do it. :D
column3: 好样的,就知道你能做到 :D

column2: If we run the simulation a few more times, success is inevitable!
Even if it takes 14 million simulations, there has to be one!
column3: 就算需要1400万次模拟,总能把它找到的!

column2: That was the last of our supplies!
column3: 这是我们最后的补给了!

column2: This time it's for real though. Good luck!
column3: 这次可是来真的.祝好运!

column2: I'm here to control the simulation.
column3: I'm here to control the simulation.

column2: Do you want me to restart it?
Alright, let's give it another shot!
Phew, good thing that one wasn't a simulation!
Warning! Progress in The Flats <wavy>will not be saved!</wavy>
column3: 注意!平原区的进度<wavy>不可保存!</wavy>

column2: If you quit or leave the area during a run, you will have to restart!
column3: 如果走出这个区域,您的进度会清零!

column2: Keep at it kiddo. You're lucky that last run was just a simulation.
column3: 继续试试吧,幸好那只是模拟.

column2: Here's some advice: You'll get a new supply drop every other tile.
column3: 提示:每隔一格会出现新补给.

column2: Recon is telling us that the aliens usually target the nearest robot. Ties broken randomly.
column3: Recon is telling us that the aliens usually target the nearest robot. Ties broken randomly.

column2: There's 6 waves total. Each spawns when all the enemies are defeated.
column3: 总共有6波.当前敌人被击溃后会进入下一波.

column2: You don't have to use resupplies right away. It can be helpful to hold off until a more opportune moment.
column3: 你不需要立刻用完所有补给,可以留到关键时刻.

column2: At the end of a wave, you might be able to find some time to move bad tiles out of the way.
column3: At the end of a wave, you might be able to find some time to move bad tiles out of the way.

column2: Do your best to keep your allies alive. Every unit matters in the end!
column3: Do your best to keep your allies alive. Every unit matters in the end!

column2: Here's some advice: You can swap the unit you spawn. Use the flag before the computer.
column3: 提示:电脑前的旗帜可以用来切换单位类型.

column2: Use that flag to move us to adjacent tiles!
column3: 使用.指挥旗帜.移动.机器人.至.相邻.滑块

column2: I am... dead??? Something went wrong!
Can't move to an occupied tile!
column3: 不能.移动...格子.已被.占据.

column2: New location was not one tile away!
